@Guru_GyanKhoji My current use case is interfacing with a database which can store/return arbitrary #RStats objects

There's still the concept of "rows" & "columns" returned by an SQL query so data.frame structure relevant. But element types may be different along a column. Hence, #ListFrames

Row/col nature of SQL results fits #RStats 'data.frame' structure, but the heterogeneous objects require list cols

How do you 
* create such a data structure in base R? 
* mutate it easily? 
* display it meaningfully? 
* manipulate + convert it?

Hence my #ListFrames exploration

For those wondering "Why listframes?", here's my motivating example from {sqlitecore}

{sqlitecore} is a wrapper around SQLite with "seamless" storage of #RStats objects

SQL query results (in row/col format) can contain heterogeneous R objects
